The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically the problem of listing all maximal cliques in a graph. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the degeneracy of graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the focus on sparse graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG).
